This paper deals with the task of semantic analysis and understanding over data of different modalities, such as natural language, graphics, and images, which are all relevant to the fields of natural language processing (NLP), machine learning (ML), and computer vision (CV). The paper proposes a neural machine for top-down generation of tree structures, which is a common data structure used in NLP and ML tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a recursive model, which is a common technique in deep learning and neural networks, making cs.LG (Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also uses a neural machine for generation, which is a common technique in AI, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also uses a model that can be applied to different modalities, including graphics and images, which are relevant to the field of CV, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses a model that can be utilized as a tree-structured decoder, which is a common technique in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category.
